<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a03b250-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6107"><num value="6107">§ 6107.</num><heading> Report to Congress</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 2 years after <date date="2006-10-17">October 17, 2006</date>, the Secretary shall submit to Congress a report on the results and effectiveness of the program carried out under this chapter, including recommendations concerning how the chapter might be improved and whether the program should be continued.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a03b251-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/247/s8">Pub. L. 106–247, § 8</ref>, <date date="2000-07-20">July 20, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/596">114 Stat. 596</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/363/tIII/s302/g">Pub. L. 109–363, title III, § 302(g)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-17">Oct. 17, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/2076">120 Stat. 2076</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
